      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEAUDIENE HUNTER NZ (3) is back from a break of four-and-a-half months and looks to be right up to the mark following a placing in a recent trial. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw and will have plenty of admirers. ARTISTIC SCRIBE (1) ran seventh last start at Pinjarra over 1684m, beaten 14 metres. Expecting a very good run from the favourable draw. ADMIRAL DARCY (7) won two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he broke and finished 20 metres away in fifth over 2130m at this track. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back. IL BANDITO (2) is worth some thought based on his victory over 2190m at Northam two runs ago. One for the multiples.",
